Reproduces a bug where update_files uses column.primary_key directly from the
protobuf instead of ColumnMetadata::is_primary. This causes _fivetran_id
(with primary_key=false) to be placed in the SET clause rather than the WHERE
clause during updates, while replace_files and delete_files correctly treat it
as a primary key. The result is that updates match too broadly and can modify
wrong rows when duplicate natural PKs exist with distinct _fivetran_id values.
